comments: Gobert (MIN) brings his arm toward the ball on his contest and some contact occurs as he brushes Allen's (CLE) arm while completing the dunk attempt.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Okoro's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
LeVert (CLE) brings his hand toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Edwards' (MIN) arm before he starts his drive.
Gobert (MIN) grasps and then quickly releases Allen's (CLE) jersey before Allen sets his intended pick.
Gobert (MIN) grasps and quickly releases Allen's (CLE) arm as marginal contact occurs before Allen slips the pick to roll.
Okoro (CLE) makes contact with the ball to deflect the rebound away from Reid (MIN).
Okoro (CLE) briefly brings his arm toward Reid's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs during Reid's drive.
Okoro (CLE) retreats alongside Reid's (MIN) path and absorbs the marginal contact as he slides his hand off Reid's (MIN) body during the driving shot attempt.
McDaniels (MIN) brings his arm toward Allen's (CLE) back and immediately removes it as marginal contact occurs when he goes over the pick.
McDaniels (MIN) legally contests Garland's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
LeVert (CLE) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) grabs and pulls Allen's (CLE) jersey away from his body, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Gobert (MIN) is assessed an unsportsmanlike technical foul.
Reid (MIN) legally contests and cleanly blocks Garland's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
The shot clock expires and a 24 second violation is correctly assessed.
Okoro (CLE) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
During the inbound, Okoro (CLE) and Edwards (MIN) mutually engage and disengage with one another as marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Okoro (CLE) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot attempt.

Garland (CLE) moves into and initiates contact to Conley's (MIN) body, which affects Conley's SQBR at the end of the drive. A non-shooting foul is correctly assessed and the basket is not scored because the illegal contact occurs before Conley's upward shooting motion on a play that ends outside the lower defensive box.
Garland (CLE) reaches across Conley's (MIN) arm and initiates illegal contact during his driving shot attempt.
McDaniels (MIN) has his arm wrapped around Allen's (CLE) body at the start of Allen's upward shooting motion, which affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Allen (CLE) brings his arm toward Conley's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as they immediately disengage during the drive.
Niang (CLE) fails to establish a legal guarding position with his right leg extended out into McDaniels' (MIN) path, which affects the play at the basket.
Conley (MIN) cleanly deflects Niang's (CLE) pass attempt and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Garland (CLE) does not extend his forearm to deliver contact to McDaniels (MIN) as they run alongside each other up the court.
Reid (MIN) initiates contact with Allen's (CLE) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Wade (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position alongside and avoids any contact with Edwards' (MIN) arms during the dunk attempt.
McDaniels (MIN) initiates contact with Allen's (CLE) body, which affects his SQBR.
Reid (MIN) establishes himself in Okoro's (CLE) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Allen (CLE) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Okoro (CLE) legally contests Reid's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
